                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1017.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 4, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Haitian Minister at Washington has received from Charles Zamor telegraphic
                    request that United States protect his departure from Port au Prince. This was
                    communicated to the Department unofficially. In accordance with this request you
                    are instructed to protect Charles Zamor and other Cabinet ministers together
                    with their families and personal belongings and insure unmolested departure for
                    them from the country, should they desire to leave. Protection may also be
                    afforded them in Port au Prince should they decide to remain.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
